    "recap_headline": "University of St. Thomas Athletics",
    "recap_text": "USAFA\u00a0COLO.-\nSt. Thomas\u00a0falls 20-12 to Air Force on Monday afternoon.\nMatthew Maulik\nled the way with five RBIs for the\u00a0Tommies\u00a0while\u00a0freshman\nTerek Verhage\nwas just\u00a0behind with\u00a0four.\nScoring Summary:\nThe Falcons\u00a0opened up\u00a0the scoring in the bottom of the second scoring two on a\u00a0two-run\u00a0homerun.\nMatthew Maulik\nand the\u00a0Tommies\u00a0responded in the top half of the third when Maulik's cleared the bases with a three run double to put the\u00a0Tommies\u00a0up 3-2.\nAir\u00a0Force then plated three in the home half of the third to take a 5-2 lead over the\u00a0Tommies.\u00a0The Falcons then extended their lead by plating seven in the fourth to take a 12-3 lead.\nSt. Thomas then plated\u00a0four\u00a0of their own in the fifth.\nMatthew Maulik\nand\nMax Berrisford\neach picked up an\u00a0RBI,\u00a0and\nTerek Verhage\ntallied two of his own.\nThe Falcons then responded by plating two in\u00a0the bottom\u00a0half of the fifth, taking a 14-7 lead.\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0put up another four\u00a0spot\u00a0in the sixth to claw back and make the score 14-11.\u00a0Verhage\u00a0picked\u00a0and Maulik picked up the RBIs once again.\nAir\u00a0Force then put up five in the bottom of the sixth to increase their lead to 19-11.\u00a0The Falcons then scored another in the seventh, taking a 20-11 lead.\nAdam Puder\ndoubled in the eighth to score\u00a0Berrisford\u00a0who also doubled, making the score 20-12 Falcons.\nUp Next:\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0return to Summit League play March 20-22 at Oral Roberts.\nFollow Along:\nAny and all information\u00a0pertaining to\u00a0the St. Thomas baseball team can be found at tommiesports.com and on Twitter @TommieBase and Instagram at @TommieBaseball."
